                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In n(omine) D(omi)ni. Constat me <persName key="#Archdeacons"><name
                                ref="Becio">Becio</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Archdeacons">archidiac(o)n(us)</rs>
                        <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/1498" key="#Churches">s(an)c(t)e <placeName
                                ref="#places/485">Cumiacl(e)n(sis)</placeName> Eccl(esi)e</orgName>,
                        iubente domno <persName key="#Bishops" ref="#people/1571"
                            >Ioh(anne)s</persName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">ep(iscopu)s</rs> s(uprascrip)te s(an)c(t)e
                        Cumiacl(e)ns(i)s Eccl(esi)e, accepisse et accepi a vob(is) <persName><name
                                ref="Albinus">Albin(us)</name></persName> p(res)b(ite)r <rs
                            key="#Rent_in_money">pensionem</rs> de una <rs key="#Houses"
                            >mansione</rs> cu(m) <rs key="#Landed_possessions">curte</rs> iuxta se
                        habente q(ui) e(st) p(o)s(i)t(a) in Cumiaclo, in regione <orgName
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1481">S(an)c(t)e Marie q(ui) v(o)c(atur)
                            Fermosa</orgName>, que p(er) <rs key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis"
                            >henfiteusin</rs> tenere viso estis at iura n(ost)ra <rs key="#Churches"
                            >eccl(esi)a</rs>, om(n)iq(ue) ann(o) in festivitate s(an)c(t)i Cassiani
                            <rs key="#Rent_in_money">p(e)n(sionem) d(e)n(ariorum) III
                            t(an)t(um)</rs>. Unde p(ro) munimine v(est)ro feci vob(is) hoc deaccepto
                        in m(en)se aug(usto), post transacta indic(tione) usq(ue) in ista quarta,
                            <placeName ref="#places/485">Cumiaclo</placeName>.</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
